TestFront is the easiest way to create end-to-end tests without code. Record your actions while you build your app and play them back to test it.

After installing this extension, open your web browser's developer tools and you'll see a new tab at the top called "TestFront".

You can use TestFront DevTools with any web page using local storage mode, but if you're using it to test your own application(s), you should commit your tests to your project's repository. See https://github.com/testfront-io/testfront-devtools for more information.
